From: Krishnakumar <krishnakumarx.kulakarni@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 6 Apr 2021 17:28:56 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 032/109] Board ID & Soc ID bitfields are updated to read
 proper board ID and Soc Id

Signed-off-by: Krishnakumar <krishnakumarx.kulakarni@intel.com>
---
 drivers/misc/hddl_device/hddl_device.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/hddl_device/hddl_device.c b/drivers/misc/hddl_device/hddl_device.c
index 1ae0cdefa929..8571f70f0361 100644
--- a/drivers/misc/hddl_device/hddl_device.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/hddl_device/hddl_device.c
@@ -391,7 +391,7 @@ int intel_hddl_register_xlink_i2c_adap(struct device *dev,
 
 		memset(&xlink_i2c_info, 0, sizeof(xlink_i2c_info));
 		xlink_i2c_info.name = "i2c_xlink";
-		xlink_i2c_info.id = c->board_info.board_id << 4 |
+		xlink_i2c_info.id = c->board_info.board_id << 5 |
 					soc_id << 2 | i;
 		c->xlink_i2c_ch[i] =
 			c->i2c_chan_num + (soc_id * 2) + i;
